**GANYMEDE ISO*


Start round one for the Release now.
To make testing easy and complete, I collect some information first on how exactly we do testing here.

**Every Desktop plus i3-wm:**
Desktop testing can be done in VM every Desktop should get tested at least one time briefly, for install itself and indeed also the installed Desktop itself should get tested.
This is to check every Desktop option and confirm they are fully working, we do not need to test every scenario with every Desktop, to test the other options you can choose a desktop freely. We only need some tests against Nvidia and non-Nvidia Driver installs for the main Desktops to check if wayland sessions working properly with Nvidia Drivers.
<small> i mean that we do not need to test every Desktop for all other possible options on partitioning and encryption and bootloaders, this is not in relation to the installed Desktops and only need to get tested in general not with every single Desktop. And we do need to test Desktops for the Nvidia Option and without Nvidia option aside from other options. </small>

1. wallpaper is set correctly
2. welcome starting automatically
3. theme is set to dark (excluding LXDE/LXQT)
4. Terminal font is monospace
5. basic functionality: Filebrowser, Media-Player, Picture-Viewer, text Editor etc

**Bootloader:**
Testing against Partition Options: Encrypted/Non-Encrypted, Aside/Replace/Erase/Manual

1. Systemd-Boot
2. Grub
3. no Bootloader once top see if it works.
4. Legacy // Grub

**Nvidia:**
That’s about the new way we boot the ISO basically, as now the ISO is auto-detecting what Nvidia Modules package it needs, and it is installing on boot of the ISO, if users choose the Nvidia boot option. And as before, in this case it will install the same Nvidia modules package on the target too.  We need to test:

1. New Nvidia GPU\`s 30xx 40xx 50xx should install and use nvidia-open modules on Live Session
2. Older 20xx and lower should use nvidia (non open Modules) on live Session
3. Nouveau: 40xx 50xx could still have issues booting on nouveau all others should boot fine with the default boot option. (no Nvidia Modules should be used on Live session and on installed OS)

**Wifi/Broadcom**
Brodcam-wl package is removed from the ISO, in case it is needed it should show a popup that lets you resolve this on the Live-Session, and in case also install broadcom-wl on targets. (only if in use/installed on live-session)

